                                <locus from="1r" to="12v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <title type="desc">Calendar</title>
                                <note>
                                    <p> Notable feasts:</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: St William of Bourges (10 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>: St Bonitus of Clermont (15 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>: St Venerandus of Clermont (18 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1v" to="1v" scheme="folios"/>: St Preiectus of Clermont (26 Jan.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: St Antholianus (6 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2r" to="2r" scheme="folios"/>: St Desideratus of Clermont (11 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="2v" to="2v" scheme="folios"/>: St Trigidius of Clermont (16 Feb.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="4v" to="4v" scheme="folios"/>: St Robert of Auvergne (24 Apr.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: St Serenus of Billom (?) (2 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5r" to="5r" scheme="folios"/>: translation of St William of Bourges (7 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>: St Cassius of Clermont (15 May);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="5v" to="5v" scheme="folios"/>: St Lupus of Limoges (22 May);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Florus of Lodève (1 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: St Genesius of Clermont (3 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6r" to="6r" scheme="folios"/>: translation of St Bonitus (6 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="6v" to="6v" scheme="folios"/>: St Abraham of Clermont (15 June);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="7r" to="7r" scheme="folios"/>: St Gallus of Clermont (1 July);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="7r" to="7r" scheme="folios"/>: St Cyril (9 July);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9r" to="9r" scheme="folios"/>: St Frodoaldus (<quote>Fredaldus</quote>; 4 Sep.) </p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="9v" to="9v" scheme="folios"/>: St Rusticus of Clermont (24 Sep.);</p>
                                    <p/>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="10v" to="10v" scheme="folios"/>: St Amabilis of Clermont (19 Oct.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Agricola and Vitalis (4 (Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Amandinus of Clermont (<quote>Amandi</quote>; 7 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Austremonius (8 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11r" to="11r" scheme="folios"/>: St Quintinianus of Clermont (10 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="11v" to="11v" scheme="folios"/>: translation of Agricola and Vitalis (27 Nov.);</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="12r" to="12r" scheme="folios"/>: St Nectarius of Auvergne (<quote>Necterei</quote>; 9 Dec.).</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="3v" to="3v" scheme="folios"/>: the ascender of the <quote>d</quote> in <quote>Benedicti</quote> is embellished with a scroll.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="8r" to="8r" scheme="folios"/>: St Romanus is placed on August 8 rather than 9, and for the remainder of August, the feasts are early by one day (or two) compared to the common dates.</p>
                                </note>
