                            </handDesc>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink; rubrics in red; capitals touched in red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="112r" to="112r" scheme="folios"/>: decorated initial over 5 lines, one in red, one in blue, with foliate patterns in gold on a blue or red background outlined in black and floral patterns in gold paint on the background and in the counter space.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="41r" to="41r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="76r" to="76r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="115v" to="115v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="122r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="125v" to="125v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="132r" to="132r" scheme="folios"/>: illuminated foliate initial over 4-5 lines in blue and red with patterns in white and outlined in black on a background of gold leaf outlined in black and vine stems with leaves in red, blue and mauve in the counter space.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="52v" to="52v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="63v" to="63v" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="70r" to="70r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="102r" to="102r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="109r" to="109r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="119r" to="119r" scheme="folios"/>, <locus from="130r" to="130r" scheme="folios"/>: illuminated foliate initial over 4-5 lines in blue and red with patterns in white and outlined in black on a background of gold leaf outlined in black and floral motifs in the same style as the border decoration on an ochre background in the counter space.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="136r" scheme="folios"/>: plain text initials over 2-3 lines in gold paint on a square background outlined in black and floral patterns in gold paint in the counter space.</p>
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="130v" scheme="folios"/>: plain sentence initials over 1 line in gold paint on a square background outlined in black and floral patterns in gold paint in the counter space. Line fillers in the same style.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="images">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="13r" to="13r" scheme="folios"/>: the Assumption; <locus from="41r" to="41r" scheme="folios"/>: the Nativity; <locus from="52v" to="52v" scheme="folios"/>: the Visitation; <locus from="63v" to="63v" scheme="folios"/>: the Annunciation; <locus from="70r" to="70r" scheme="folios"/>: Joachim and Anna meeting at the Golden Gate; <locus from="76r" to="76r" scheme="folios"/>: Job; <locus from="102r" to="102r" scheme="folios"/>: a funeral; <locus from="109r" to="109r" scheme="folios"/>: the Crucifixion (Calvary); <locus from="112r" to="112r" scheme="folios"/>: Pentecost; <locus from="115v" to="115v" scheme="folios"/>: the Trinity; <locus from="119r" to="119r" scheme="folios"/>: the stoning of St Stephen; <locus from="122r" to="122r" scheme="folios"/>: a bishop; <locus from="125v" to="125v" scheme="folios"/>: St Catherine piercing a regent (Maxentius?) with her sword; <locus from="130r" to="130r" scheme="folios"/>: the Virgin Mary with the
                                        Christ Child and two angels; <locus from="132r" to="132r" scheme="folios"/>: the Mourning of Christ / Pietà. The miniatures are surrounded by border decoration with floral motifs in blue, green, red, pink, gold paint, some gold leaf, and tendrils in black. The opening of the individual hours are also accompanied by border decorations in the same style, but mainly restricted to foliage in blue, yellow and green, in panels extending the length of the right margin and half of the upper and lower margin. According to a former librarian, the style of the decoration reveals Flemish influence. For further discussion of the decoration, see <ref target="http://urn.kb.se/resolve?urn=urn:nbn:se:alvin:portal:record-472874">Lindqvist Sandgren</ref>.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                                <decoNote type="bookmarks">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="SR1v" to="SR1v" scheme="other"/>: Two booksmarks of woven green silk thread.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
                        </physDesc>
